Ford Motor Co said it extendedits current buyer incentive program on selected cars and lighttrucks to April Six.    It also said it added the Ford Taurus and Mercury Sable tothe program which gives customers a choice of 3.9- to9.9-annual percentage rate financing.    Ford said buyers of all 1986 and 1987 Taurus and Sablemodels can choose between the low financing rates or cashallowances of 400 dlrs.    Buyers of all other eligible cars will get a cash allowanceof up to 600 dlrs, plus the low financing rates. It said thosebuying trucks can choose between the low financing or a cashrebate of up to 600 dlrs.    Ford said the program takes effect now and applies to mostvehicles delivered to retail customers from dealer stock. Aprogram for Mustang ends March 31 as announced earlier. Reuter&#3;